WEBVTT

00:01.274 --> 00:04.075
Why am I being suspended?
I didn't leak any documents.

00:04.391 --> 00:06.392
You were unfairly punished,

00:06.444 --> 00:08.778
and I would like
to officially welcome you back.

00:08.863 --> 00:10.280
- I want a raise.
- Fine.

00:10.364 --> 00:12.499
And Pearson Hardman pays for
law school when I decide to go.

00:12.566 --> 00:13.700
Agreed.

00:13.751 --> 00:16.085
- I fronted your buy-in.
- How could you do that?

00:16.170 --> 00:17.570
You were about to take
a job somewhere else.

00:17.622 --> 00:19.923
We need to start being honest
with each other.

00:20.007 --> 00:21.124
You want me off this case,

00:21.209 --> 00:22.926
so I don't get anywhere
near the spotlight.

00:23.010 --> 00:24.177
In your position,

00:24.245 --> 00:26.579
the spotlight can become
an interrogation lamp

00:26.631 --> 00:27.964
pretty damn fast.

00:28.049 --> 00:30.100
This is always
how it's gonna be, isn't it?

00:30.184 --> 00:31.468
I thought you knew that.

00:31.552 --> 00:33.470
I guess I did.

00:33.554 --> 00:34.675
I need you to use your power

00:34.722 --> 00:36.189
to give me this case
over Scottie.

00:36.257 --> 00:39.142
Are you asking as a friend,
or are you calling in a chit?

00:39.227 --> 00:40.610
Calling in a chit.

00:40.695 --> 00:42.696
Does this have something to do
with that favor he did you?

00:42.763 --> 00:44.364
- Yes.
- Tell me what it is.

00:44.431 --> 00:45.482
I can't.

00:45.566 --> 00:46.483
Guess we're not
sharing everything

00:46.567 --> 00:48.368
with each other after all.

00:50.137 --> 00:53.073
[Funk music]

00:53.124 --> 01:01.081
♪

01:04.718 --> 01:06.136
Time to wake up, sweetie.

01:06.220 --> 01:08.955
Oh, five more minutes, mom.

01:09.006 --> 01:10.623
Did you just call me mom?

01:10.675 --> 01:12.475
What? No.

01:12.560 --> 01:14.344
Louis,
I've said it before.

01:14.428 --> 01:17.847
The bedroom
is a no-mom-talk zone.

01:17.932 --> 01:19.015
Understood.

01:19.100 --> 01:21.968
- You have to catch your train.
- [Groans]

01:22.019 --> 01:23.469
I'll take the later one.

01:23.521 --> 01:24.854
Who are you,

01:24.939 --> 01:27.073
and what have you done
with my boyfriend, Louis Litt?

01:27.141 --> 01:28.358
Oh, you mean the guy

01:28.442 --> 01:30.994
who sweats profusely
before closing arguments?

01:31.078 --> 01:32.495
- Yeah.
- Yeah, that guy's gone.

01:32.580 --> 01:34.814
[Laughs]
Really?

01:34.865 --> 01:37.701
Oh, my God.

01:37.785 --> 01:40.153
You're completely dry.

01:40.204 --> 01:41.921
Your love has made me dry,
Sheila.

01:41.989 --> 01:44.874
[Both laugh]

01:44.959 --> 01:46.293
I'm a changed man.

01:46.344 --> 01:49.179
In fact...
I'm gonna rock your world

01:49.263 --> 01:51.264
for one more hour, and then I'm
gonna kick some ass in court.

01:51.332 --> 01:52.999
'Cause today
nothing can go wrong.

01:53.050 --> 01:54.500
Today is my goddamn day.

01:54.552 --> 01:57.220
Yeah. It is.
[Giggles]

01:57.305 --> 02:04.728
♪

02:04.812 --> 02:08.315
[Sighs]

02:08.366 --> 02:09.866
Can you pass the sugar?

02:09.949 --> 02:12.452
Yeah, of course.

02:12.519 --> 02:16.573
Okay, how 'bout that milk?

02:16.657 --> 02:18.024
Sounds great.

02:18.075 --> 02:19.242
How would you feel
about me dating other women

02:19.327 --> 02:21.861
now that we're
living together and all?

02:21.912 --> 02:23.380
Pizza's perfect.

02:23.464 --> 02:24.864
[Snaps]
Rachel.

02:24.915 --> 02:26.466
What's going on?

02:26.533 --> 02:29.386
I got my tuition
payment schedule, and...

02:29.470 --> 02:31.704
Wow.
That is a big bill.

02:31.756 --> 02:33.590
Yeah, and that's
not even the problem.

02:33.674 --> 02:35.041
Remember when Louis fired me

02:35.092 --> 02:36.926
because he thought
that I was leaking information?

02:37.011 --> 02:38.928
I never told you about

02:39.013 --> 02:39.929
negotiating the terms
of my return.

02:40.014 --> 02:41.314
Yeah, you did.

02:41.382 --> 02:43.817
He gave you a 10% raise.
That's not all he gave me.

02:43.884 --> 02:45.268
He agreed that the firm
would pay for me

02:45.353 --> 02:46.552
to go to law school
when I got in.

02:46.604 --> 02:47.604
So what's the problem?

02:47.688 --> 02:49.939
It's gonna be
an awkward conversation.

02:50.024 --> 02:51.408
Rachel,
you want to be a lawyer,

02:51.492 --> 02:53.526
you're gonna have to have
a lot of awkward conversations.

02:53.577 --> 02:54.861
Yeah, but not like this.

02:54.912 --> 02:56.229
I mean, "Hey, Louis,
do you remember when I demanded

02:56.280 --> 02:57.997
"that you pay for me
to go to law school?

02:58.065 --> 03:00.333
"I get that since then you've
now tried to help me get in

03:00.401 --> 03:01.501
"and that we're friends,

03:01.568 --> 03:03.703
but I would really
like my money now."

03:03.754 --> 03:05.255
Okay.
So don't talk to him.

03:05.339 --> 03:08.958
Just get ready to write
a check for $200,000,

03:09.043 --> 03:11.928
because that's what it's gonna
cost for the next three years.

03:12.012 --> 03:14.597
- Awkward conversation it is.
- Best of luck.

03:14.682 --> 03:15.765
Oh.

03:15.850 --> 03:17.634
Norma, it's Louis.

03:17.718 --> 03:19.936
Louis Litt, your boss.

03:20.020 --> 03:21.221
Don't play your games
with me now, woman.

03:21.272 --> 03:23.273
I'm due for closing arguments
30 minutes,

03:23.357 --> 03:24.607
and I need you to stall.

03:24.692 --> 03:28.611
No, you do not pull the fire
alarm as a tactic, okay?

03:28.696 --> 03:30.280
I need you to just
buy me ten minutes

03:30.364 --> 03:31.648
without committing a crime.

03:31.732 --> 03:33.566
Taxi!

03:33.617 --> 03:37.737
There we go.
Come on, baby. My man.

03:37.788 --> 03:39.823
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no, no,
don't you upstream me.

03:39.907 --> 03:41.624
That's my cab.
That's my taxi.

03:41.709 --> 03:43.776
This is my cab.
This is my cab.

03:43.828 --> 03:46.663
Hey, I'm gonna sue you.
I'm gonna sue you for sucking.

03:46.747 --> 03:48.027
I'm gonna sue you
for not being--

03:48.082 --> 03:51.501
okay, I need your name,
date of birth, and I need--

03:51.585 --> 03:54.454
all right, let's Litt this up.

03:57.258 --> 04:00.143
[Elevator dings]

04:00.227 --> 04:01.678
Uhoh.
What did you do to Scottie?

04:01.762 --> 04:03.430
- Nothing.
- That is not nothing.

04:03.481 --> 04:06.433
That is a soy caramel latte with
a double shot of fear and guilt.

04:06.484 --> 04:08.518
That is an apology coffee.

04:08.602 --> 04:10.770
Why can't it just be an
"I'm a great boyfriend" coffee?

04:10.821 --> 04:12.138
If you're
such a great boyfriend,

04:12.189 --> 04:14.324
why don't you know that
your girlfriend is on her way

04:14.408 --> 04:15.525
to Chicago
for the Wexler deposition?

04:15.609 --> 04:19.529
- Oh, shit.
- So I repeat, what did you do?

04:19.613 --> 04:21.814
I overruled her
on Franklin Courier.

04:21.866 --> 04:23.500
I made her give the case
back to Louis.

04:23.584 --> 04:25.485
[Sighs]
You got in the middle of it?

04:25.536 --> 04:26.920
Why would you do that?

04:26.987 --> 04:28.004
Look, I don't want to get
into it right now, Donna.

04:28.088 --> 04:29.255
Okay.

04:29.323 --> 04:32.041
But, Harvey, if you really did
do that to her,

04:32.126 --> 04:34.844
coffee isn't gonna cut it.

04:37.214 --> 04:41.468
For the record,
this was not my goal.

04:43.187 --> 04:44.837
Mr. Litt.

04:44.889 --> 04:47.056
Sorry, Your Honor.
Sorry I'm late.

04:47.141 --> 04:48.674
Are you ready
for closing arguments?

04:48.726 --> 04:52.529
Yes, I am.

04:52.613 --> 04:55.198
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

04:55.282 --> 04:58.368
opposing counsel has accused my
client of a great many things.

04:58.452 --> 05:00.353
But you see,
here's the problem.

05:00.404 --> 05:05.291
They don't have one single fact
to back up their claim.

05:05.359 --> 05:07.043
I mean, not one.

05:07.127 --> 05:08.828
So you know what I'm gonna do?
I'm gonna challenge you.

05:08.879 --> 05:10.296
Actually, no, scratch that.

05:10.364 --> 05:12.665
I'm gonna dare you
to find dispute

05:12.716 --> 05:15.552
with the facts of this case
as we presented them.

05:15.636 --> 05:16.886
'Cause are you a good person?

05:16.971 --> 05:18.304
Yes.

05:18.372 --> 05:21.140
Are you a good person?
Yes.

05:21.208 --> 05:23.676
Are you--actually, you took
notes, so I can see you care.

05:23.727 --> 05:27.430
You see, this is the kind
of jury that they teach about.

05:27.515 --> 05:30.567
This is the kind of jury
that's gonna hear me

05:30.651 --> 05:32.185
when I say these four words.

05:32.236 --> 05:33.719
Do you know
what those four words are?

05:33.771 --> 05:36.322
Because I want you
to remember these four words

05:36.390 --> 05:37.907
to your dying breath.

05:37.992 --> 05:41.411
He didn't do it!

05:41.495 --> 05:42.895
He didn't do it.

05:42.947 --> 05:45.898
[Heart beating]

05:49.670 --> 05:53.540
Mr. Litt, are you okay?

05:53.591 --> 05:57.343
I'm all right.
Yeah, I'm fine.

05:57.411 --> 05:59.295
[Groans]

06:01.715 --> 06:05.585
Bailiff, call an ambulance.

06:05.636 --> 06:09.272
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:09.356 --> 06:12.609
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:12.693 --> 06:15.778
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:15.863 --> 06:19.566
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:19.617 --> 06:22.535
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

